    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the President’s Secretary</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tully</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-15">September 15,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MRout1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MR-out</hi>
                    </gloss>-412. Personal and secret to Miss Grace Tully from Harry Hopkins.</p>
                <p>I sent to the President memorandum entitled French Lend Lease Agreement and dated
                    September 11th from the State Department.<note n="1" xml:id="d247fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_419">p. 419</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_FEA1">FEA</gloss> and State Department are anxious to know
                    whether the President has initialed it.</p>
                <p>Could you help me get an answer on this tomorrow?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry Hopkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
